SIMPLE: petrified
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: petrified
<hw>petrified</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Converted into
stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Converted into a mineral; <as>as, <ex>petrified</ex>
wood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mineralized.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Same as <er>terrified</er>; <as>as,
<ex>petrified</ex> by the sight of the approaching bear</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> panicky, panic-stricken, panic-struck, terrified,
frightened.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>rendered unable to act due to intense fear.</def>
<illu><ex>petrified</ex> with fear</illu>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> frozen.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Rendered lifeless or inactive; <as>as, an
imagination <ex>petrified</ex> by habitual television
viewing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> frozen; ossified.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petrify</ent>⟦br⟧
